com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.configs

Class ConfigsRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Configs>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.configs.ConfigsRequestExecutor

  • public class ConfigsRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Configs>
    Request executor provided by ConfigsApi. Use this class if you want to obtain configs through fluent API in chained fashion. Here is an example of how to use this executor: 
       
   IKontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloud.newInstance();
   Configs configs = kontaktCloud.configs().fetch()
      .type(DeviceType.BEACON)
      .profile(DeviceProfile.EDDYSTONE)
      .maxResult(15)
      .execute();
    Keep in mind that device type must be specified so invocation of type method is mandatory. Otherwise an exception will be thrown.
